WEBVTT

00:00.840 --> 00:01.480
4.

00:21.180 --> 00:27.720
And as they spake unto the people, the priests, and the captain of the temple, and the Sadducees

00:27.720 --> 00:34.060
came upon them, being grieved that they taught the people, and preached through Jesus the

00:34.060 --> 00:35.680
resurrection from the dead.

00:36.300 --> 00:41.860
And they laid hands on them, and put them in hold unto the next day, for it was now

00:41.860 --> 00:42.840
even tide.

00:43.540 --> 00:49.780
Howbeit many of them which heard the word believed, and the number of the men was about

00:49.780 --> 00:50.680
five thousand.

00:51.520 --> 00:58.020
And it came to pass on the morrow, that their rulers, and elders, and scribes, and Annas

00:58.020 --> 01:04.920
the high priest, and Caiaphas, and John, and Alexander, and as many as were of the kindred

01:04.920 --> 01:08.560
of the high priest, were gathered together at Jerusalem.

01:09.100 --> 01:16.420
And when they had set them in the midst, they asked, By what power, or by what name have

01:16.420 --> 01:17.440
ye done this?

01:17.440 --> 01:26.060
Then Peter, filled with the Holy Ghost, said unto them, Ye rulers of the people, and elders

01:26.060 --> 01:35.080
of Israel, If we this day be examined of the good deed done to the impotent man, by what

01:35.080 --> 01:43.560
means he is made whole, be it known unto you all, and to all the people of Israel, that

01:43.560 --> 01:51.460
by the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth, whom ye crucified, whom God raised from the dead,

01:51.840 --> 01:56.320
even by him doth this man stand here before you whole.

01:57.380 --> 02:05.340
This is the stone, which was set at naught of you builders, which is become the head

02:05.340 --> 02:12.360
of the corner, neither is there salvation in any other, for there is none other name

02:12.360 --> 02:16.920
under heaven given among men, whereby we must be saved.

02:18.200 --> 02:24.720
Now when they saw the boldness of Peter and John, and perceived that they were unlearned

02:24.720 --> 02:27.960
and ignorant men, they marveled.

02:28.320 --> 02:34.520
And they took knowledge of them, that they had been with Jesus, and beholding the man

02:34.520 --> 02:39.540
which was healed standing with them, they could say nothing against it.

02:39.540 --> 02:46.460
But when they had commanded them to go aside out of the council, they conferred among

02:46.460 --> 02:50.660
themselves, saying, What shall we do to these men?

02:51.080 --> 02:56.800
For that indeed a notable miracle hath been done by them is manifest to all them that

02:56.800 --> 02:59.760
dwell in Jerusalem, and we cannot deny it.

03:00.340 --> 03:06.800
But that it spread no further among the people, let us straightly threaten them, that they

03:06.800 --> 03:10.060
speak henceforth to no man in this name.

03:10.840 --> 03:18.380
And they called them, and commanded them not to speak at all nor teach in the name of Jesus.

03:19.380 --> 03:25.160
But Peter and John answered and said unto them, Whether it be right in the sight of

03:25.160 --> 03:29.280
God to hearken unto you more than unto God, judge ye.

03:30.000 --> 03:34.660
For we cannot but speak the things which we have seen and heard.

03:35.360 --> 03:40.520
So when they had further threatened them, they let them go, finding nothing how they

03:40.520 --> 03:42.880
might punish them, because of the people.

03:43.260 --> 03:46.540
For all men glorified God for that which was done.

03:47.500 --> 03:53.420
For the man was above forty years old, on whom this miracle of healing was shewed, and

03:53.420 --> 04:00.600
being let go, they went to their own company, and reported all that the chief priests and

04:00.600 --> 04:02.540
elders had said unto them.

04:03.380 --> 04:10.000
And when they heard that, they lifted up their voice to God, with one accord, and said,

04:10.360 --> 04:20.040
Lord, thou art God, which hast made heaven, and earth, and the sea, and all that in them

04:20.040 --> 04:28.100
is, who by the mouth of thy servant David hast said, Why did the heathen rage?

04:28.660 --> 04:31.640
And the people imagined vain things.

04:32.180 --> 04:38.620
The kings of the earth stood up, and the rulers were gathered together against the Lord, and

04:38.620 --> 04:40.080
against his Christ.

04:41.920 --> 04:49.500
For of a truth against thy holy child Jesus, whom thou hast anointed, both Herod and Pontius

04:49.500 --> 04:55.900
Pilate with the Gentiles and the people of Israel were gathered together, for to do whatsoever

04:55.900 --> 04:59.920
thy hand and thy counsel determined before to be done.

05:01.140 --> 05:07.700
And now, Lord, behold their threatenings, and grant unto thy servants, that with all

05:07.700 --> 05:14.940
boldness they may speak thy word, by stretching forth thine hand to heal, and that signs and

05:14.940 --> 05:18.940
wonders may be done by the name of thy holy child Jesus.

05:19.500 --> 05:26.260
And when they had prayed, the place was shaken where they were assembled together, and they

05:26.260 --> 05:33.240
were all filled with the Holy Ghost, and they spake the word of God with boldness.

05:34.320 --> 05:40.960
And the multitude of them that believed were of one heart and of one soul, neither said

05:40.960 --> 05:46.660
any of them that ought of the things which he possessed was his own, but they had all

05:46.660 --> 05:53.180
common, and with great power gave the apostles witness of the resurrection of the Lord Jesus,

05:53.860 --> 05:56.780
and great grace was upon them all.

05:57.640 --> 06:03.320
Neither was there any among them that lacked, for as many as were possessors of lands or

06:03.320 --> 06:10.000
houses sold them, and brought the prices of the things that were sold, and laid them down

06:10.000 --> 06:16.140
at the apostles' feet, and distribution was made unto every man according as he had need.

06:16.720 --> 06:23.360
And Joses, who by the apostles was surnamed Barnabas, which is being interpreted the son

06:23.360 --> 06:31.520
of Consolation, a Levite, and of the country of Cyprus, having land, sold it, and brought

06:31.520 --> 06:34.640
the money, and laid it at the apostles' feet.

06:35.160 --> 06:40.520
Chapter 5 But a certain man named Ananias, with Sapphira

06:40.520 --> 06:48.100
his wife, sold a possession, and kept back part of the price, his wife also being privy

06:48.100 --> 06:53.220
to it, and brought a certain part, and laid it at the apostles' feet.

06:53.760 --> 07:02.880
But Peter said, Ananias, why hath Satan filled thine heart to lie to the Holy Ghost, and

07:02.880 --> 07:05.920
to keep back part of the price of the land?

07:06.580 --> 07:09.280
Whilst it remained, was it not thine own?

07:09.500 --> 07:13.580
And after it was sold, was it not in thine own power?

07:14.200 --> 07:17.200
Why hast thou conceived this thing in thine heart?

07:17.620 --> 07:22.020
Thou hast not lied unto men, but unto God.

07:23.000 --> 07:30.960
And Ananias, hearing these words, fell down, and gave up the Ghost, and great fear came

07:30.960 --> 07:33.560
on all them that heard these things.

07:34.580 --> 07:40.640
And the young men arose, wound him up, and carried him out, and buried him.

07:41.340 --> 07:47.260
And it was about the space of three hours after, when his wife, not knowing what was

07:47.260 --> 07:54.760
done, came in, and Peter answered unto her, Tell me, whether ye sold the land for so much?

07:55.760 --> 07:57.820
And she said, Yea, for so much.

07:58.620 --> 08:05.440
Then Peter said unto her, How is it that ye have agreed together to tempt the Spirit of

08:05.440 --> 08:06.280
the Lord?

08:06.600 --> 08:13.000
Behold, the feet of them which have buried thy husband are at the door, and shall carry

08:13.000 --> 08:14.080
thee out.

08:14.880 --> 08:20.060
Then fell she down, straightway at his feet, and yielded up the Ghost.

08:20.360 --> 08:27.800
And the young men came in, and found her dead, and carrying her forth, buried her by her

08:27.800 --> 08:28.220
husband.

08:29.400 --> 08:35.780
And great fear came upon all the church, and upon as many as heard these things.

08:36.580 --> 08:41.920
And by the hands of the apostles were many signs and wonders wrought among the people.

08:42.800 --> 08:46.400
And they were all with one accord in Solomon's porch.

08:47.140 --> 08:53.560
And of the rest there's no man joined himself to them, but the people magnified them.

08:54.080 --> 09:01.560
And believers were the more added to the Lord multitudes both of men and women, insomuch

09:01.560 --> 09:07.380
that they brought forth the sick into the streets, and laid them on beds and couches,

09:07.760 --> 09:12.980
that at the least the shadow of Peter passing by might overshadow some of them.

09:13.560 --> 09:19.500
There came also a multitude out of the cities round about unto Jerusalem, bringing sick

09:20.180 --> 09:23.860
and them which were vexed with unclean spirits.

09:24.780 --> 09:26.660
And they were healed every one.

09:27.460 --> 09:33.000
Then the high priest rose up, and all they that were with him, which is the sect of the

09:33.000 --> 09:39.960
Sadducees, and were filled with indignation, and laid their hands on the apostles, and

09:39.960 --> 09:41.780
put them in the common prison.

09:42.500 --> 09:48.860
But the angel of the Lord by night opened the prison doors, and brought them forth,

09:49.380 --> 09:56.380
and said, Go, stand and speak in the temple to the people all the words of this life.

09:56.840 --> 10:02.060
And when they heard that, they entered into the temple early in the morning, and taught.

10:02.740 --> 10:08.380
But the high priest came, and they that were with him, and called the council together,

10:08.380 --> 10:14.920
and all the senate of the children of Israel, and sent to the prison to have them brought.

10:16.340 --> 10:22.980
But when the officers came, and found them not in the prison, they returned and told,

10:23.180 --> 10:30.620
saying, The prison truly found we shut, with all safety, and the keepers standing without

10:30.620 --> 10:31.760
before the doors.

10:32.120 --> 10:35.920
But when we had opened, we found no man within.

10:36.800 --> 10:41.980
Now when the high priest and the captain of the temple, and the chief priests heard these

10:41.980 --> 10:45.760
things, they doubted of them whereunto this would grow.

10:47.160 --> 10:53.520
Then came one, and told them, saying, Behold, the men whom ye put in prison, are standing

10:53.520 --> 10:56.120
in the temple, and teaching the people.

10:56.920 --> 11:01.640
Then went the captain with the officers, and brought them without violence, for they feared

11:01.640 --> 11:04.040
the people, lest they should have been stoned.

11:04.640 --> 11:09.700
And when they had brought them, they set them before the council, and the high priest asked

11:09.700 --> 11:15.100
them, saying, Did not we straightly command you that ye should not teach in this name?

11:15.260 --> 11:23.180
And behold, ye have filled Jerusalem with your doctrine, and intend to bring this man's

11:23.180 --> 11:24.600
blood upon us.

11:25.060 --> 11:31.420
Then Peter and the other apostles answered, and said, We ought to obey God rather than

11:31.420 --> 11:31.900
men.

11:32.360 --> 11:38.500
The God of our fathers raised up Jesus, whom ye slew, and hanged on a tree.

11:39.020 --> 11:47.560
Him hath God exalted with his right hand, to be a prince and a savior, for to give repentance

11:47.560 --> 11:50.640
to Israel, and forgiveness of sins.

11:51.580 --> 11:59.680
And we are his witnesses of these things, and so is also the Holy Ghost, whom God hath

11:59.680 --> 12:01.720
given to them that obey him.

12:03.180 --> 12:09.100
When they heard that, they were cut to the heart, and took counsel to slay them.

12:09.580 --> 12:17.820
Then stood thereup one in the council, a Pharisee named Gamaliel, a doctor of the law, had in

12:17.820 --> 12:24.240
reputation among all the people, and commanded to put the apostles forth a little space,

12:24.440 --> 12:31.440
and said unto them, Ye men of Israel, take heed to yourselves what ye intend to do as

12:31.440 --> 12:32.760
touching these men.

12:33.480 --> 12:40.520
For before these days rose up Theodos, boasting himself to be somebody, to whom a number of

12:40.520 --> 12:48.160
men about four hundred joined themselves, who was slain, and all as many as obeyed him

12:48.160 --> 12:50.620
were scattered and brought to naught.

12:51.500 --> 12:58.860
After this man rose up Judas of Galilee, in the days of the taxing, and drew away much

12:58.860 --> 13:00.220
people after him.

13:01.040 --> 13:07.780
He also perished, and all, even as many as obeyed him, were dispersed.

13:08.300 --> 13:14.480
And now I say unto you, Refrain from these men, and let them alone.

13:14.480 --> 13:20.280
For if this council, or this work be of men, it will come to naught.

13:21.480 --> 13:30.020
But if it be of God, ye cannot overthrow it, lest happily ye be found even to fight against

13:30.020 --> 13:30.680
God.

13:31.240 --> 13:37.880
And to him they agreed, and when they had called the apostles, and beaten them, they

13:37.880 --> 13:44.320
demanded that they should not speak in the name of Jesus, and let them go.

13:45.520 --> 13:51.340
And they departed from the presence of the council, rejoicing that they were counted

13:51.340 --> 13:54.080
worthy to suffer shame for his name.

13:55.240 --> 14:03.000
And daily in the temple, and in every house, they ceased not to teach and preach Jesus

14:03.000 --> 14:03.960
Christ.

14:04.480 --> 14:08.800
Chapter 6 And in those days, when the number of the

14:08.800 --> 14:15.960
disciples was multiplied, there arose a murmuring of the Grecians against the Hebrews, because

14:15.960 --> 14:19.320
their widows were neglected in the daily ministration.

14:20.440 --> 14:27.060
Then the twelve called the multitude of the disciples unto them, and said, It is not reason

14:27.060 --> 14:31.000
that we should leave the word of God and serve tables.

14:31.900 --> 14:37.880
Wherefore, brethren, look ye out among you, seven men of honest report, full of the Holy

14:37.880 --> 14:42.100
Ghost and wisdom, whom we may appoint over this business.

14:42.720 --> 14:48.100
But we will give ourselves continually to prayer, and to the ministry of the word.

14:49.960 --> 14:56.640
And the saying pleased the whole multitude, and they chose Stephen, a man full of faith,

14:56.640 --> 15:06.200
and of the Holy Ghost, and Philip, and Prochorus, and Nicanor, and Tymon, and Parmenes, and

15:06.200 --> 15:11.880
Nicholas, a proselyte of Antioch, whom they set before the apostles.

15:12.640 --> 15:16.220
And when they had prayed, they laid their hands on them.

15:17.120 --> 15:24.260
And the word of God increased, and the number of the disciples multiplied in Jerusalem greatly.

15:24.920 --> 15:28.880
And a great company of the priests were obedient to the faith.

15:30.040 --> 15:37.000
And Stephen, full of faith and power, did great wonders and miracles among the people.

15:39.220 --> 15:45.640
Then there arose certain of the synagogue, which is called the synagogue of the libertines,

15:45.640 --> 15:53.460
and Cyrenians and Alexandrians, and of them of Cilicia and of Asia, disputing with Stephen.

15:54.520 --> 15:59.000
And they were not able to resist the wisdom and the spirit by which he spake.

15:59.640 --> 16:07.020
Then they suborned men, which said, We have heard him speak blasphemous words against

16:07.020 --> 16:09.580
Moses and against God.

16:10.060 --> 16:17.120
And they stirred up the people, and the elders, and the scribes, and came upon him, and caught

16:17.120 --> 16:24.680
him, and brought him to the council, and set up false witnesses, which said, This man ceaseth

16:24.680 --> 16:30.380
not to speak blasphemous words against this holy place and the law.

16:30.580 --> 16:37.240
For we have heard him say that this Jesus of Nazareth shall destroy this place, and

16:37.240 --> 16:41.120
shall change the customs which Moses delivered us.

16:41.380 --> 16:48.240
And all that sat in the council, looking steadfastly on him, saw his face as it had been the face

16:48.240 --> 16:49.280
of an angel.

